data.title: Anthropic enhances security with AI Safety Level 3 protocols, specifically against CBRN threats, through Claude Opus 4.
data.description: Anthropic has implemented AI Safety Level 3 guidelines to enhance security and deployment procedures, focusing on protection against CBRN threats. This initiative accompanies the release of Claude Opus 4, aiming to strengthen defense protocols.

data.title: Dominion Energy reports Q3 2025 net income of $1.0 billion ($1.16 per share), up from $934 million ($1.09 per share) in 2024.
data.description: Dominion Energy, Inc. revealed a unaudited net income of $1.0 billion ($1.16 per share) for the three months ending Sept. 30, 2025, in accordance with Generally Accepted Accounting Principles (GAAP). This marks an increase from the net income of $934 million ($1.09 per share) reported for the same period in 2024. The operating earnings (non-GAAP) for the three months ending Sept. 30, 2025, stood at $921 million ($1.06 per share).

data.title: Clearmind Medicine files U.S. patent for neuroplastogen MEAI therapy to treat cocaine addiction.
data.description: In Vancouver, Canada, on October 31, 2025, Clearmind Medicine Inc. made an announcement regarding the publication of a U.S. patent application. Clearmind is a clinical-stage biotech company listed on Nasdaq as CMND and on FSE as CWY0. The company is dedicated to developing innovative neuroplastogen-derived therapeutics for addressing significant, yet undertreated, health issues. The patent application extends the coverage of their non-hallucinogenic compound, 5-methoxy-2-aminoindane (MEAI), specifically for combating cocaine addiction. This development signifies a significant step in Clearmind's efforts to tackle addiction problems.

data.title: Fortive CEO to present at Baird’s Global Industrial Conference on 11/11/2025 at 5:05 p.m. ET. Visit www.fortive.com for webcast.
data.description: In Everett, Washington, Fortive Corporation (NYSE: FTV) revealed that Olumide Soroye, the President and CEO, is set to speak at the Baird 2025 Global Industrial Conference on November 11, 2025, at 4:05 p.m. CT (5:05 p.m. ET). The presentation will be live-streamed on www.fortive.com and retained for later viewing. Fortive focuses on pioneering crucial technologies to ensure global safety and productivity.

data.title: Cboe Global Markets' Q3 2025: Record diluted EPS $2.85 (up 38%), adjusted diluted EPS $2.67 (up 20%), net revenue $605.5M (up 14%). Organic revenue growth target for 2025 increased.
data.description: In the third quarter, there were notable achievements with record numbers. The diluted earnings per share (EPS) stood at $2.85, marking a considerable 38% increase. Additionally, the adjusted diluted EPS for the quarter reached a record high of $2.67, showing a significant 20% rise. The net revenue for the quarter also hit a new peak at $605.5 million, indicating a notable 14% increase. Furthermore, the organic total net revenue growth target for 2025 was upgraded to 'low...'.

data.title: AGCO reports Q3 sales of $2.5B, down 4.7% YOY, with earnings per share at $4.09. Full-year outlook for adjusted EPS increased to $5.00. $300M in share repurchases planned for Q4 2025.
data.description: With net sales totaling $2.5 billion, reflecting a 4.7% decrease compared to the previous year, the company reported earnings per share of $4.09 and adjusted earnings per share of $1.35. The full-year adjusted earnings per share outlook has been raised to around $5.00. Additionally, the company plans to initiate $300 million worth of share repurchases during the fourth quarter of 2025.

data.title: Bermuda boosts insurtech at ITC Vegas 2025, highlights partnerships and regulation. Oct 31, 2025.
data.description: Bermuda demonstrated its commitment to industry collaboration at an event in Las Vegas on October 31, 2025. The delegation consisted of leaders from both the public and private sectors, highlighting partnerships in insurtech and discussions on AI regulation. This showcased Bermuda's focus on fostering collaborative efforts, with an emphasis on homegrown innovations. The event emphasized the importance of cooperation between different sectors, showing a unified approach towards driving forward the jurisdiction's initiatives.

data.title: HoldCo Asset Management presents to Eastern Bankshares board $2.6 billion assets managed - Oct. 31, 2025.
data.description: In Fort Lauderdale, Florida on October 31, 2025, HoldCo Asset Management, LP ("HoldCo"), a local investment firm overseeing around $2.6 billion in regulatory assets under management, presented to the Independent Board of Directors of Eastern Bankshares today.

data.title: Federal Realty Investment Trust reports Q3 2025 results; net income for common shareholders at $0.69 per share.
data.description: In North Bethesda, Maryland, on October 31, 2025, Federal Realty Investment Trust (NYSE:FRT) released its third-quarter results for the period ending September 30, 2025. The net income available for common shareholders for the three months ending September 30, 2025, and September 30, 2024, was $0.69 per share.
